Omg, supposedly I injured my leg. I’m also white. This person is messaging my friends and followers and posing as me, but also sending pictures that aren’t me so it’s weird (and funny). Please feel free to mess with them, enjoy the screenshots journey, but also eventually report them. It’ll help make them go away. 

Thanks @jayded_247 for being the first to mess with. I fully approve and would do the same.
I had this in my drafts and forgot to post it. Barbecue for the win.

My older sister, Sheri, lost her life to cancer last night. I still can’t believe this happened. She fought her hardest until her very last breath. She was strong, supportive, fun, selfless, beautiful, and one of my best friends. Except when we were younger and she beat me up. 

One of the last things she said to me was “you’re such a good brother.” Thank you Sheri. You were the best sister. It’s also sad talking about you in past tense now. 

Sheri, I hope I made you proud and continue making you proud. You lived life and loved life. Your heart of gold will always be a part of me, Mom, Dad, Sabrina, Ryder, Taylor, Remy, the rest of our family, your friends, and your coworkers. You will never be forgotten and I’m so sorry this happened. 

Miss you and love you ❤️

My older sister passed away a year ago today. If she were still around, she’d be like, “Why are you posting this about me”. That makes sense. She’d definitely be proud of what I’ve accomplished, but super annoyed that I posted about her passing away. 

It’s sad that her life was cut short. She did what she could and fought hard at the time to make sure she was with family for as long as possible before her last day with us. 

I think about you all the time. I see you when I look in the mirror…since I’m basically a guy version of you. 

I’m not a spiritual person, BUT if you are looking down on me, please please please just don’t do it when I’m using the restroom or taking a shower. You should know better!

Miss you. Love you. Wish you could be here with us. ❤️
